This paper deals with digital image forensics, which involves analyzing and identifying the origin and authenticity of digital images. The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for determining whether two image patches contain the same or different forensic traces. This involves feature extraction and similarity scoring, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also deals with issues related to image manipulation and forgery detection, which are relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to database consistency verification, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data management (cs.DB).
